<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>Personal Combined Feed</title><link>https://example.invalid</link><description>Personal aggregate feed</description><docs>http://www.rssboard.org/rss-specification</docs><generator>python-feedgen</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 11:59:03 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Bank of England sees growing risks to financial stability from AI</title><link>https://www.reuters.com/business/finance/bank-england-sees-growing-risks-financial-stability-ai-2026-07-07/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Article URL: &lt;a href="https://www.reuters.com/business/finance/bank-england-sees-growing-risks-financial-stability-ai-2026-07-07/"&gt;https://www.reuters.com/business/finance/bank-england-sees-growing-risks-financial-stability-ai-2026-07-07/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Comments URL: &lt;a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48816381"&gt;https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48816381&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Points: 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 0&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48816381</guid><pubDate>Tue, 07 Jul 2026 11:44:31 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Show HN: I built an in-call AI, and the hard part was making it talk less</title><link>https://heyalo.ai</link><description>&lt;p&gt;We use Attio for call recordings (tried a few other notetakers as well). And they work great... that's kind of the problem. The summary shows up with the answer to the question I couldn't answer well during the meeting. The information existed the whole time. My notes, the CRM, earlier in the same call. Just not reachable when we are busy in the meeting.&lt;p&gt;So the question we kept having: why does all this intelligence only show up after the call ends?&lt;p&gt;We tried the obvious things. LLM in a side tab doesn't work, you can't always type and listen at the same time... and it knows nothing about your call anyway. Then I built the better version, an AI commenting on the call live. But we noticed that the real importance is minimizing a cognitive load of users by minimizing interruptions during the live call.&lt;p&gt;So almost all the work went into making it talk less, think more. This is how we built Heyalo (&lt;a href="https://heyalo.ai" rel="nofollow"&gt;https://heyalo.ai&lt;/a&gt;). It listens and reasons through the whole call, speaks when something's worth a mention.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
